Cloning a gadget would copy the configs of an existing gadget, display a new gadget underneath the original, initially in "Edit" mode.

Any OAuth shenanigans will presumably still need to occur.

The issue type context calculation is incorrect:

# {{IS NOT EMPTY, != EMPTY, NOT IN (EMPTY) -> (*, \{type1, type2, type3,...,typen\})}}

It should actually be (*, *)

The project clause context is not correctly calculated when working with empty values:

# {{= EMPTY, IS EMPTY, IS NOT EMPTY, IS  -> (*, *)}}
# {{!= EMPTY, NOT IN (EMPTY) -> (\{proj1, proj2, ..., projn\}, *)}}

The issue level security context calculation is not correct when working with the negative operators. For example, consider the project configuration:

proj:one -> level:{oneadmin}
proj:two -> level:{twoonly}
proj:three -> level:{oneadmin, threeonly}
proj:four -> level:{fouronly}

Executing a query "level != oneadmin" will actually return a context of ({two, four}, *) when it should actually be ({two, three, four}, *) since there is still a security level in proj:three that can match the condition.

